insertVertex

public static IGeometry insertVertex(IGeometry geometry,
                                     java.awt.geom.Point2D newVertex,
                                     double snapTolerance)
Inserts a new vertex in a segment of the geometry boundary. It doesnt moves nothing, it only inserts a new collineaer vertex inside a segment. It is useful to make topological edition, ensuring two geometries shares a vertex.

Parameters:
geometry -
newVertex -
snapTolerance -
Returns:

smoothGeometry

public static IGeometry smoothGeometry(IGeometry originalGeometry,
                                       int curveOption)
From a given geometry with dimension 1 or 2, it computes a parametric curve and return a smoothed version of the original geometry. To draw the returned geometry it uses a usual GeneralPath, being the FLATNESS factor of the returned curve FConverter.FLATNESS.

Parameters:
originalGeometry -
Returns:
